Modifications
-------------
This distribution includes modifications to the original WebRTC code:

1. Objective-C Symbol Prefixing:
   - All public Objective-C types are prefixed with "SCX"
   - Constant type prefix changed to "kSCX"
   - Modified via RTC_OBJC_TYPE_PREFIX macro in RTCMacros.h

2. Framework Renaming:
   - Framework name changed from "WebRTC.framework" to "SmileCXWebRTC.framework"
   - Bundle identifier changed to "cx.smile.SmileCXWebRTC"

3. Build System Modifications:
   - Build configuration files modified (BUILD.gn)
   - Framework generation scripts modified (Python build tools)
   - Info.plist bundle metadata updated

Modified Files:
- sdk/objc/base/RTCMacros.h
- sdk/BUILD.gn
- sdk/objc/Info.plist
- tools_webrtc/ios/generate_umbrella_header.py
- tools_webrtc/apple/copy_framework_header.py
- tools_webrtc/ios/build_ios_libs.py

Purpose: These modifications enable symbol isolation to prevent collisions
between the Vivocha SDK and other WebRTC implementations that may be included
in customer applications.

Distribution: This modified version is distributed as a binary XCFramework
via GitHub Releases and Swift Package Manager.

